definitions.definition: An aliphatic hydrocarbon of chemical formula C 5 H 12 ; either of the three isomers n-pentane, methyl-butane ( isopentane ), and di-methyl-propane ( neopentane ); volatile liquids under normal conditions .

main_definition: ( organic chemistry ) An aliphatic hydrocarbon of chemical formula C 5 H 12 ; either of the three isomers n-pentane, methyl-butane ( isopentane ), and di-methyl-propane ( neopentane ); volatile liquids under normal conditions .
